  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Looks like `verbatim` is considered to have defaulted control flow side effects, so it's e.g. assumed not to successfully terminate a transaction.\r\n\r\nThis should either be changed or at least be clearly documented, since it is well possible to construct `verbatim` that very much does affect control flow behaviour, which would be ill-behaved for example wrt the unused store eliminator.\r\n",
  "closed_by": null,
